obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (47473)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and extent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00016_197843_1517807320451&sectionId=47473&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00016_197843_1517807320451
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Prize Chits and Money Circulation`
  line `Schemes (Banning) Act, 1978.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India ^1***`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "except the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 34 of 2019, s. 95 and the Fifth Schedule`
  line `(w.e.f. 31-10-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (47474)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00016_197843_1517807320451&sectionId=47474&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00016_197843_1517807320451
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "conventional chit" means a transaction whether called chit, chit fund, kuri or by any other`
  line `name by or under which a person responsible for the conduct of the chit enters into an agreement with`
  line `a specified number of persons that every one of them shall subscribe a certain sum of money (or`
  line `certain quantity of grain instead) by way of periodical instalments for a definite period and that each`
  line `such subscriber shall, in his turn, as determined by lot or by auction or by tender or in such other`
  line `manner as may be provided for in the chit agreement, be entitled to a prize amount.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In this clause "prize amount" shall mean the amount, by whatever name called,`
  line `arrived at by deducting from out of the total amount paid or payable at each instalment by all the`
  line subscribers,
  line
  line `(i) the commission charged as service charges as a promoter or foreman or an agent; and`
  line
  line `(ii) any sum which a subscriber agrees to forego, from out of the total subscriptions of each`
  line `instalment, in consideration of the balance being paid to him;`
  line
  line `(b) "money" includes a cheque, postal order, demand draft, telegraphic transfer or money order;`
  line
  line `(c) "money circulation scheme" means any scheme, by whatever name called, for the making of`
  line `quick or easy money, or for the receipt of any money or valuable thing as the consideration for a`
  line `promise to pay money, on any event or contingency relative or applicable to the enrolment of`
  line `members into the scheme, whether or not such money or thing is derived from the entrance money of`
  line `the members of such scheme or periodical subscriptions;`
  line
  line `(d) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(e) "prize chit" includes any transaction or arrangement by whatever name called under which a`
  line `person collects whether as a promoter, foreman, agent or in any other capacity, monies in one lump`
  line `sum or in instalments by way of contributions or subscriptions or by sale of units, certificates or other`
  line `instruments or in any other manner or as membership fees or admission fees or service charges to or`
  line `in respect of any savings, mutual benefit, thrift, or any other scheme or arrangement by whatever`
  line `name called, and utilises the monies so collected or any part thereof or the income accruing from`
  line `investment or other use of such monies for all or any of the following purposes, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) giving or awarding periodically or otherwise to a specified number of subscribers as`
  line `determined by lot, draw or in any other manner, prizes or gifts in cash or in kind, whether or not`
  line `the recipient of the prize or gift is under a liability to make any further payment in respect of such`
  line `scheme or arrangement;`
  line
  line `(ii) refunding to the subscribers or such of them as have not won any prize or gift, the whole`
  line `or part of the subscriptions, contributions or other monies collected, with or without any bonus,`
  line `premium, interest or other advantage by whatever name called, on the termination of the scheme`
  line `or arrangement, or on or after the expiry of the period stipulated therein,`
  line
  line `but does not include a conventional chit;`
  line
  line `(f) "Reserve Bank" means the Reserve Bank of India constituted under the Reserve Bank of India`
  line `Act, 1934 (2 of 1934).`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (47487)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Banning of prize chits and money circulation schemes or enrolment as members or participation therein.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00016_197843_1517807320451&sectionId=47487&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00016_197843_1517807320451
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `No person shall promote or conduct any prize chit or money circulation scheme,`
  line `or enroll as a member to any such chit or scheme, or participate in it otherwise, or receive or remit any`
  line `money in pursuance of such chit or scheme.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (47476)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Penalty for contravening the provisions of section 3.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00016_197843_1517807320451&sectionId=47476&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00016_197843_1517807320451
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `Whoever contravenes the provisions of`
  line `section 3 shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to three years, or with fine`
  line `which may extend to five thousand rupees, or with both:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the absence of special and adequate reasons to the contrary to be mentioned in the`
  line `judgment of the court, the imprisonment shall not be less than one year and the fine shall not be less than`
  line `one thousand rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (47477)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Penalty for other offences in connection with prize chits or money circulation schemes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00016_197843_1517807320451&sectionId=47477&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00016_197843_1517807320451
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, with a view to the promotion or conduct of any prize chit or money circulation scheme in`
  line `contravention of the provisions of this Act or in connection with any chit or scheme promoted or`
  line `conducted as aforesaid,--`
  line
  line `(a) prints or publishes any ticket, coupon or other document for use in the prize chit or money`
  line `circulation scheme; or`
  line
  line `(b) sells or distributes or offers or advertises for sale or distribution, or has in his possession for`
  line `the purpose of sale or distribution any ticket, coupon or other document for use in the prize chit or`
  line `money circulation scheme; or`
  line
  line `(c) prints, publishes or distributes, or has in his possession for the purpose of publication or`
  line distribution--
  line
  line `(i) any advertisement of the prize chit or money circulation scheme; or`
  line
  line `(ii) any list, whether complete or not, of members in the prize chit or money circulation`
  line `scheme; or`
  line
  line `(iii) any such matter descriptive of, or otherwise relating to the prize chit or money`
  line `circulation scheme, as is calculated to act as an inducement to persons to participate in that prize`
  line `chit or money circulation scheme or any other prize chit or money circulation scheme; or`
  line
  line `(d) brings, or invites any person to send, for the purpose of sale or distribution, any ticket, coupon`
  line `or other document for use in a prize chit or money circulation scheme or any advertisement of such`
  line `prize chit or money circulation scheme; or`
  line
  line `(e) uses any premises, or causes or knowingly permits any premises to be used, for purposes`
  line `connected with the promotion or conduct of the prize chit or money circulation scheme; or`
  line
  line `(f) causes or procures or attempts to procure any person to do any of the above-mentioned acts,`
  line
  line `shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to two years, or with fine which may`
  line `extend to three thousand rupees, or with both:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the absence of special and adequate reasons to the contrary to be mentioned in the`
  line `judgment of the court, the imprisonment shall not be less than one year and the fine shall not be less than`
  line `one thousand rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (47478)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00016_197843_1517807320451&sectionId=47478&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00016_197843_1517807320451
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an offence under this Act has been committed by a company,`
  line `every person who, at the time the offence was committed, was in charge of, and was responsible to, the`
  line `company for the conduct of the business of the company, as well as the company, shall be deemed to be`
  line `guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment provided in this Act, if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or`
  line `that he exercised all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where an offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a company and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent or`
  line `connivance of, or is attributable to, any neglect on the part of, any director, manager, secretary or other`
  line `officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall also be deemed to be guilty`
  line `of that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section--`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means any body corporate and includes a firm or other association of`
  line `individuals; and`
  line
  line `(b) "director", in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (47479)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Power to enter, search and seize.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00016_197843_1517807320451&sectionId=47479&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00016_197843_1517807320451
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) It shall be lawful for any police officer not below the rank`
  line `of an officer in charge of a police station,--`
  line
  line `(a) to enter, if necessary by force, whether by day or night with such assistance as he considers`
  line `necessary, any premises which he has reason to suspect, are being used for purposes connected with`
  line `the promotion or conduct of any prize chit or money circulation scheme in contravention of the`
  line `provisions of this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) to search the said premises and the persons whom he may find therein;`
  line
  line `(c) to take into custody and produce before any Judicial Magistrate all such persons as are`
  line `concerned or against whom a complaint has been made or credible information has been received or a`
  line `reasonable suspicion exists of their having been concerned with the use of the said premises for`
  line `purposes connected with, or with the promotion or conduct of, any such prize chit or money`
  line `circulation scheme as aforesaid;`
  line
  line `(d) to seize all things found in the said premises which are intended to be used, or reasonably`
  line `suspected to have been used, in connection with any such prize chit or money circulation scheme as`
  line aforesaid.
  line
  line `(2) Any officer authorised by the State Government in this behalf may--`
  line
  line `(a) at all reasonable times, enter into and search any premises which he has reason to suspect, are`
  line `being used for the purposes connected with, or conduct of, any prize chit or money circulation`
  line `scheme in contravention of the provisions of this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) examine any person having the control of, or employed in connection with, any such prize chit`
  line `or money circulation scheme;`
  line
  line `(c) order the production of any documents, books or records in the possession or power of any`
  line `person having the control of, or employed in connection with, any such prize chit or money`
  line `circulation scheme; and`
  line
  line `(d) inspect and seize any register, books of account, documents or any other literature found in`
  line `the said premises.`
  line
  line `(3) All searches under this section shall be made in accordance with the provisions of the Code of`
  line `Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (47480)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Forfeiture of newspaper and publication containing prize chit or money circulation scheme.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00016_197843_1517807320451&sectionId=47480&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00016_197843_1517807320451
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `Where any newspaper or other publication contains any material connected with any prize chit`
  line `or money circulation scheme promoted or conducted in contravention of the provisions of his Act or any`
  line `advertisement in relation thereto, the State Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `declare every copy of the newspaper and every copy of the publication containing such material or the`
  line `advertisement to be forfeited to the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (47481)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Power to try offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00016_197843_1517807320451&sectionId=47481&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00016_197843_1517807320451
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `No court inferior to that of a Chief Metropolitan Magistrate, or as the`
  line `case may be, Chief Judicial Magistrate, shall try any offence punishable under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (47482)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Offences under this Act to be cognizable.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00016_197843_1517807320451&sectionId=47482&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00016_197843_1517807320451
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `All offences punishable under this Act shall be`
  line cognizable.
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (47483)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Act not to apply to certain prize chits or money circulation schemes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00016_197843_1517807320451&sectionId=47483&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00016_197843_1517807320451
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `Nothing contained in`
  line `this Act shall apply to any prize chit or money circulation scheme promoted by--`
  line
  line `(a) a State Government or any officer or authority on its behalf; or`
  line
  line `(b) a company wholly owned by a State Government which does not carry on any business other`
  line `than the conducting of a prize chit or money circulation scheme whether it is in the nature of a`
  line `conventional chit or otherwise; or`
  line
  line `(c) a banking company as defined in clause (c) of section 5 of the Banking Regulation`
  line `Act, 1949 (10 of 1949), or a banking institution notified by the Central Government under section 51`
  line `of that Act or the State Bank of India constituted under section 3 of the State Bank of India`
  line `Act, 1955 (23 of 1955), or a subsidiary bank constituted under section 3 of the State Bank of India`
  line `(Subsidiary Banks) Act, 1959 (38 of 1959), or a corresponding new bank constituted under section 3`
  line `of the Banking Companies (Acquisition and Transfer of Undertakings) Act, 1970 (5 of 1970), or a`
  line `Regional Rural Bank established under section 3 of the Regional Rural Banks Act, 1976 (21 of 1976),`
  line `or a co-operative bank as defined in clause (bii) of section 2 of the Reserve Bank of India`
  line `Act, 1934 (2 of 1934); or`
  line
  line `(d) any charitable or educational institution notified in this behalf by the State Government, in`
  line `consultation with the Reserve Bank.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (47484)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Transitional provisions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00016_197843_1517807320451&sectionId=47484&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00016_197843_1517807320451
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, a person`
  line `conducting a prize chit or money circulation scheme at the commencement of this Act may continue to`
  line `conduct such chit or scheme for such period as may be necessary for the winding up of the business`
  line `relating to such chit or scheme, so however that such period shall not in any case extend beyond a period`
  line `of two years from such commencement:`
  line
  line `Provided that the said person shall furnish to the State Government or to such officer as may be`
  line `authorised by it in this behalf and to such office of the Reserve Bank as may be prescribed in such form`
  line `and within such period as may be prescribed, full information regarding the chit or scheme along with a`
  line `winding up plan prepared in accordance with the provisions of any rules that may be made by the State`
  line `Government in this behalf under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided further that if the State Government is satisfied, on an application made by the person`
  line `conducting the prize chit or money circulation scheme, that the chit or scheme cannot be wound up within`
  line `the period fixed in the winding up plan furnished to the State Government under the foregoing proviso, it`
  line `may, in consultation with the Reserve Bank, permit such person to continue to conduct the business`
  line `relating to the said chit or scheme for such further period as may be considered necessary having regard to`
  line `the circumstances of the case and the interests of the members of the said chit or scheme.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government may, in consultation with the Reserve Bank, approve the winding up plan`
  line `furnished under sub-section (1) with or without modifications or reject the same and may grant or refuse`
  line `to grant permission to continue to conduct that chit or scheme:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such winding up plan shall be modified or rejected without giving an opportunity of`
  line `being heard to the person who conducts such prize chit or money circulation scheme.`
  line
  line `(3) If any person fails to furnish full information regarding the said chit or scheme along with its`
  line `winding up plan in the form and within the period prescribed, he shall forfeit his right to continue the`
  line `business relating to the said chit or scheme on the expiry of such period.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in any agreement or arrangement entered into`
  line `between any person conducting any such chit or scheme and the subscriber, the person conducting the`
  line `chit or scheme shall, within such period as may be prescribed, refund the monies or the subscriptions`
  line `collected till the date of default referred to in sub-section (3).`
  line
  line `(5) If any person fails to comply with the provisions of sub-section (4), he shall be punishable with`
  line `imprisonment for a term which may extend to two years, or with fine which may extend to three thousand`
  line `rupees, or with both:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the absence of special and adequate reasons to the contrary to be mentioned in the`
  line `judgment of the court, the imprisonment shall not be less than one year and the fine shall not be less than`
  line `one thousand rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (47485)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 4 of 1986, s. 2 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 15-5-1986).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00016_197843_1517807320451&sectionId=47485&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00016_197843_1517807320451
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette`
  line `and in consultation with the Reserve Bank, make rules for the purpose of carrying out the provisions of`
  line `this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for--`
  line
  line `(a) the office of the Reserve Bank to whom full information regarding any prize chit or money`
  line `circulation scheme may be furnished under the first proviso to sub-section (1) of section 12, and the`
  line `form in which and the period within which such information may be furnished;`
  line
  line `(b) the particulars relating to the winding up plan of the business relating to prize chits or money`
  line `circulation schemes.`
  line
  line `^1[(3) Every rule made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before the`
  line `State Legislature.]`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (47486)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Repeals and saving.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00016_197843_1517807320451&sectionId=47486&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00016_197843_1517807320451
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Andhra Pradesh Money Circulation Scheme (Prohibition)`
  line `Act, 1965 (Andhra Pradesh Act 30 of 1956), as in force in the State of Andhra Pradesh, and in the`
  line `Union territory of Chandigarh and the Madhya Pradesh Dhan Parichalan Skeem (Pratishedh)`
  line `Adhiniyam, 1975 (Madhya Pradesh Act 19 of 1975), are hereby repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding the repeal of any Act referred to in sub-section (1), anything done or any action`
  line `taken under the provisions of any such Act shall, in so far as such thing or action is not inconsistent with`
  line `the provisions of this Act, be deemed to have been done or taken under the provisions of this Act as if the`
  line `said provisions were in force when such thing was done or such action was taken and shall continue in`
  line `force accordingly until superseded by anything done or any action taken under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
